<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36189b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36189b">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36189b"> 189(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hide of bullock</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The learned Dominie Heckwelder records a tradition that the Dutch discoverers bargained for only so much land as the <mark>hide of a bullock</mark> would cover; but that they cut the hide in strips no thicker than a child&apos;s finger, so as to take in a large portion of land, and to take in the Indians into the bargain. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 54</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
